The paper deals with scheduling jobs on distributed clusters of parallel machines, which is a problem in distributed computing (cs.DC). The use of Map-Reduce computing framework and the scale of the datasets suggest that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The scheduling problem itself involves optimization and combinatorial aspects, which are relevant to the sub-category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The development of approximation algorithms and LP relaxations suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of computational complexity (cs.CC) and machine learning (cs.LG).
